This PR adds a few lemmas (in particular `le_of_zpow_le_zpow_of_lt_one₀`  and `eq_zero_of_zpow_eq_one₀`) to `Algebra.Order.GroupWithZero.Canonical`.

Used in project Formalization of the Bruhat-Tits Tree.

Co-authored-by: Christian Merten <christian@merten.dev>

Thanks for the lemmas! As previously stated, `LinearOrderedCommGroupWithZero` and all its files are on their way to being deprecated because all lemmas can be generalised to also include linear ordered semifields. Here are indications on how to generalise everything.
This can be made an iff, is true under the mere assumptions `[MonoidWithZero M₀] [Nontrivial M₀]`, and should be located in `Algebra.GroupWithZero.Basic` just after `zero_pow_eq`
Ok, I made it an iff and moved it to the place you suggested.
This can be made an iff, is true under the mere assumptions `[GroupWithZero M₀] [Nontrivial M₀]`, and should be located in `Algebra.GroupWithZero.Basic` just after `zero_zpow_eq`
made it into an iff statement, and moved it to the suggested place.
This is a special case of `zpow_lt_zpow_right_of_lt_one₀` and should be deleted

I'm confused. The conclusion of your lemma [zpow_lt_zpow_right_of_lt_one](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Order/GroupWithZero/Unbundled.html#zpow_lt_zpow_right_of_lt_one%E2%82%80)₀ is `a ^ n ≤ a ^ m`, and not 
`a ^ n < a ^ m `. 
(From the name I would have expected the conclusion to be `a ^ n < a ^ m `.)
I do want the version with strict inequality.
Whoops, looks like a typo. It should say `<`. Feel free to fix it in this PR.

I think your lemma [zpow_lt_zpow_right_of_lt_one₀](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Order/GroupWithZero/Unbundled.html#zpow_lt_zpow_right_of_lt_one%E2%82%80) is in fact lemma [zpow_le_zpow_right_of_le_one₀](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Order/GroupWithZero/Unbundled.html#zpow_le_zpow_right_of_le_one%E2%82%80).

I have fixed this, so that `zpow_lt_zpow_of_lt_one₀` is what it should be.
This is superseded by `zpow_le_zpow_iff_right₀` and should be deleted
deleted lemma
This can be made an iff, should be called `zpow_lt_zpow_iff_right_of_lt_one₀` and should be proved and located similarly to `zpow_lt_zpow_iff_right₀`
done, but could you please explain what "right" in the name means?
This can be made an iff, weakened to `a ≠ 1`, and should be proved using and moved close to `zpow_right_inj₀`
done.

```suggestion
lemma zero_pow_eq_one₀ [Nontrivial M₀] : (0 : M₀) ^ n = 1 ↔ n = 0 := by
```

```suggestion
  rw [zero_pow_eq, zero_ne_one.ite_eq_left]
```
Your suggestion doesn't seem to work.

```suggestion
lemma zero_zpow_eq_one₀ {n : ℤ} : (0 : G₀) ^ n = 1 ↔ n = 0 := by
```

```suggestion
  rw [zero_zpow_eq, zero_ne_one.ite_eq_left]
```
same here, I'm getting an error message if I try the code

Oh the lemma is called `Ne.ite_eq_left_iff`, so I guess
```suggestion
  rw [zero_zpow_eq, zero_ne_one.ite_eq_left_iff]
```

```suggestion
lemma zpow_eq_one₀ (ha₀: 0 <= a) (ha₁ : a ≠ 1) {n : ℤ} : a ^ n = 1 ↔ n = 0 := by
```
and can you please remove the `a = 0` special case you are introducing in this PR?

Sorry, writing from phone
I don't understand. I am assuming `0 < a` in the lemma.

Yes, but it's also true for `a = 0` (as per your lemma above), so you can generalise the proof 😉

I would simply start the proof with `obtain rfl | ha := ha.eq_or_lt`, reprove your above lemma in the first branch and move your current proof to the second branch

```suggestion
  simpa using zpow_right_inj₀ ha₀ ha₁ (n := 0)
```
